ai_summary.en: With the BTC Fear & Greed Index signaling "Extreme Fear" (20), the broader crypto market remains deeply apprehensive. Whales on Ethereum, representing institutional capital, exhibit a surprisingly neutral to slightly positive sentiment (0.09) with substantial stablecoin inflows, suggesting cautious accumulation or rebalancing within a high-volume environment. In stark contrast, Solana's retail and speculative money shows a clear bearish sentiment (-0.29) and significant stablecoin outflows amidst much lower volume, indicating continued de-risking. This divergence points to a short-term outlook of continued caution, where smart money might be accumulating blue-chips while retail exits speculative assets until macro sentiment improves.
ai_summary.zh: 随着BTC恐惧与贪婪指数处于“极度恐惧”（20），整个加密市场情绪依旧低迷。代表机构资金的以太坊鲸鱼表现出令人惊讶的中性到略微积极的情绪（0.09），伴随着大量稳定币流入和高交易量，暗示着谨慎的积累或资产再平衡。相比之下，Solana上的散户和投机资金呈现明显的看跌情绪（-0.29），并在低交易量下出现显著的稳定币流出，表明持续的去风险化。这种分歧预示着短期内市场将持续谨慎，精明资金可能在积累蓝筹股，而散户则在宏观情绪改善前退出投机性资产。
